LAGOS – It was mixed feelings on Friday when the draws for the quarterfinals and semifinals of the UEFA Champions League (UCL) was held. Holders Chelsea FC have been drawn against Real Madrid in the UEFA Champions League (UCL) quarterfinals, while Manchester City will take on Atletico Madrid and Liverpool FC play Benfica. Bayern Munich face Villarreal in the other last-eight tie. Chelsea and Man City would meet in the semifinals if they both overcome their Madrid opposition, while Liverpool could meet Bayern in the last four. The Blues overcame Real in last season’s semifinals en route to winning the competition, while Atletico face a swift return to Manchester having just eliminated Man United in the round of 16. Many football pundits are of the view that Jurgen Klopp’s men have the dream route to the final in Paris.The two-leg quarterfinals take place on April 5-6 and 12-13 while the first legs of the semifinals will be on April 26-27 and the second legs on May 3-4. The Stade de France in Paris will host the final on Saturday, May 28 after it was moved from St Petersburg after Russia’s invasion of Ukraine. The draw means Chelsea face a reunion with their former manager Carlo Ancelotti, who won the English Premier League (EPL) and FA Cup double during a two-year spell with the Stamford Bridge club between 2009 and 2011. The Italian is one of only three managers to win the UEFA Champions League (UCL) three times, including with Real in 2014, and returned for a second spell at the Spanish giant’s last summer after leaving Everton.Chelsea and Real also met at the semifinal stage last season, with Thomas Tuchel’s side winning 3-1 on aggregate before going on to beat Manchester City in the final. POLL Atletico Madrid have the chance to complete a Manchester double after being drawn against Pep Guardiola’s City, with Diego Simeone’s side having beaten Manchester United 2-1 on aggregate in the quarterfinals.